HTML CheatSheet Tags With Explanation

1.<!DOCTYPE> 	Defines the document type

2.<html>	Defines the root of an HTML document

3.<head>	Contains metadata/information for the document

4.<body>	Defines the document's body

5.<main>	Specifies the main content of a document

6.<header>  Defines a header for a document or section

7.<section> Defines a section in a document

8.<span>   Defines a section in a document

9.<article> tag specifies independent, self-contained content.

10.<aside> tag defines some content aside from the content it is placed in.

11.<a> tag defines a hyperlink, which is used to link from one page to another.

12. <h1> to <h6> Defines HTML headings

13.<br> tag inserts a single line break.

14.<button> tag defines a clickable button.

15.<footer> tag defines a footer for a document or section.

16.<form> tag is used to create an HTML form for user input.

17.<hr> tag defines a thematic break in an HTML page 

18.<input> tag specifies an input field where the user can enter data.

19.The <li> tag defines a list item.

20.<nav> tag defines a set of navigation links.

21.<script> tag is used to embed a client-side script

22.<strong> tag is used to define text with strong importance

23.<style> tag is used to define style information (CSS) for a document.

24.<table> tag defines an HTML table.

25.<tbody> tag is used to group the body content in an HTML table

26.<td> tag defines a standard data cell in an HTML table.

27.<th> tag defines a header cell in an HTML table.

28.<title> tag defines the title of the document.

29.<tr> tag defines a row in an HTML table

30.<!--...-->	Defines a comment

31.<b>	Defines bold text

32.<em> tag is used to define emphasized text

33.<i>	Defines a part of text in an alternate voice or mood

34.<iframe>	Defines an inline frame,inline frame is used to embed another document within the current HTML document

35.<q>	Defines a short quotation

36.<blockquote>	Defines a section that is quoted from another source.

37.<address>	Defines contact information for the author/owner of a document.

38.<div>	Defines a section in a document

39.<audio>	Defines embedded sound content

40.<video>	Defines embedded video content

<input type="text" spellcheck="value"> the Spell Check feature can be applied to HTML forms using the spellcheck attribute

Detailed Descriptions

A.Lists

<ul> Creates an unordered list

<ol> Creates an ordered list 

<li> Encompasses each list item

<dl> Creates a definition list

<dt> Precedes each defintion term

<dd> Precedes each defintion

Ex.dl>
  <dt>Coffee</dt>
  <dd>Black hot drink</dd>
  <dt>Milk</dt>
  <dd>White cold drink</dd>
</dl>

B.HTML Attributes

All HTML elements can have attributes
Attributes provide additional information about elements
Attributes are always specified in the start tag
Attributes usually come in name/value pairs like: name="value"

1.href
The <a> tag defines a hyperlink. The href attribute specifies the URL of the page the link goes to:

2.src
The <img> tag is used to embed an image in an HTML page. The src attribute specifies the path to the image to be displayed

3.width and height
specifies the width and height of the image

4.alt attribute for the <img>
tag specifies an alternate text for an image

<img src="img_typo.jpg" alt="Girl with a jacket">

5.style
attribute is used to add styles to an element
<p style="color:red;">

6.lang attribute inside the <html>
declare the language of the Web page
<html lang="en">

7.title
attribute defines some extra information about an element

8.Using The class Attribute

The class attribute is often used to point to a class name in a style sheet

Ex:<div class="city">

9.Using The Id Attribute

The id attribute specifies a unique id for an HTML element.

Difference Between Class and ID

A class name can be used by multiple HTML elements, while an id name must only be used by one HTML element within the page:

10.SpellCheck Attribute
<input type="text" spellcheck="value"> the Spell Check feature can be applied to HTML forms using the spellcheck attribute

11..contenteditable attribute
The contenteditable attribute specifies whether the content of an element is editable or not.

12.Dir

Dir attribute of HTML sets the direction of the text within an element in HTML

13.accept 

The accept attribute specifies a filter for what file types the user can pick from the file input dialog box (only for type="file").

14.align

Th align Attribute is used to specify the alignment of applet, caption, col, colgroup, hr, iframe, img, table, tbody, td, tfoot , th, thead, tr applet, area, img, input text content.

15.async 

A script that will be run asynchronously as soon as it is available

16.autocomplete 

The autocomplete attribute specifies whether a form or an input field should have autocomplete on or of

17.autofocus 

When present, it specifies that an <input> element should automatically get focus when the page loads.

18.autoplay 

The autoplay attribute is a boolean attribute.
When present, the audio/video will automatically start playing as soon as it can do so without stopping.

19.autosave 

The autosave attribute is a non-standard attribute that enables the persistence of search terms across page reloads

20.bgcolor

The HTML bgcolor attribute is used to set the background color of an HTML element.

21.buffered 

The buffered property returns a TimeRanges object.
The TimeRanges object represents the user's buffered ranges of the audio/video

22.challenge 
The challenge attribute specifies that the value of the <keygen> element will be challenged when submitted.

The <keygen> tag specifies a key-pair generator field used for forms.

23.charset 

The charset attribute specifies the character encoding used in an external script file.

ISO-8859-1" - Standard encoding for the Latin alphabet
"UTF-8" - Character encoding for Unicode. Compatible with ASCII


24.checked 

The checked attribute is a boolean attribute.

25.cite

The HTML cite attribute is used to specify the URL of the document that explains the quotes, message or text which describes why the text was inserted. 


What is .htaccess?
.htaccess is a configuration file for use on web servers running the Apache Web Server software.